A web server handles HTTP/HTTPS requests and serves static content like:

HTML
CSS
Images

It’s mainly responsible for delivering web pages

Examples:
Apache HTTP Server
Nginx

An application server handles business logic and generates dynamic content.

It:

Processes user input
Interacts with databases
Runs backend code (Java, Python, etc.)

Examples:

Apache Tomcat
JBoss EAP

Interview:
A web server serves static content and handles HTTP requests, while an application server processes business logic, interacts with databases, and generates dynamic responses.

Feature	                      Web Server	                  Application Server
Purpose	                      Serve static content	        Handle business logic
Content	                      Static (HTML, CSS)	          Dynamic (generated data)
Processing	                  Minimal	                      Heavy processing
Database Interaction	        No	                          Yes
Role	                        Frontend delivery	             Backend processing

How They Work Together

In real-world systems:

Client sends request
Web server receives it
If static → responds directly
If dynamic → forwards to application server
App server processes → sends response back
